metadata.dc:description: We want to present an urethral prolapse, in an elderly woman, after a physical effort. This situation is rarely reported in the literature, being a more common situation in children and premenarchal girls. The most common presentation is genital mass and bleedding. If it is a large one can become strangulated and urinary symptoms are present as acute urine retention. We want to describe the surgical treatment.
metadata.dc:title: Prolapso uretral tras esfuerzo físico. Corrección quirúrgica.
[Urethral prolapse following physical effort. Surgical repair].
